# Implementation Plan: High-Fidelity Accident Detection & Response System (SURE)

This implementation plan outlines the reverse engineering of the "Accident Detection on Indian Roads" project and the creation of a high-fidelity, clickable web prototype based on the actual components found in the ZIP.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The prototype will be built entirely as a static, client-side web application in the workspace root. All Python CLI and Android App functions will be converted into high-fidelity frontend simulation layers. This enables instant deployment, interactive demonstrations (ideal for hackathons and academic presentations), and standalone execution without local server dependencies.

---

## 1. Summary of Reverse Engineered Project Components

### A. Files Analyzed
1. **Model Specs**: `Python Demo/graph/pipeline.config` (defines training pipeline configurations), `Python Demo/accidents.pbtxt` (class labels).
2. **Python Demo**: `Python Demo/classifier.py` (CLI classifier), `Python Demo/run.log` (execution warnings and outputs).
3. **Android Client**: `Android App/app/src/main/.../roadaccidents/MainActivity.java` (UI controller), `Classifier.java` (interface), `TensorFlowImageClassifier.java` (TF Mobile inference logic), `activity_main.xml` (layout view), `label_strings.txt` (labels).
4. **Static UI Templates**: `index.html`, `style.css`, `app.js` (existing project base to be refactored).

### B. Original Project Features & Configuration
- **Model Architecture**: Single Shot Multibox Detector (SSD) with MobileNetV1 backbone (`ssd_mobilenet_v1`).
- **Input Dimensions**: 300x300 pixels, RGB.
- **Dataset Labels**: ID 1 corresponds to `'car accident'`. Background class is `???`.
- **Classification Threshold**: Default set to 60% (`0.6f` in Android client; adjustable in Python client via NMS score converters).
- **Execution Workflow**:
  - **Python Demo CLI**: Takes inputs via `python classifier.py [Input Image] [Output Image]` and saves the image overlaying predicted boxes, outputting `done. Detections found: 1 \n Accident score: 99.99%`.
  - **Android Client**: Displays a 300x300 camera frame, a 75x75 thumbnail of the resized bitmap, a text field printing detections string arrays (like `[1] car accident (78.3%)`), and a manual "Detect Object" button.

