## 2. Proposed Modules & Pages to Generate

We will organize the application into **8 major views** selectable from a premium, animated sidebar navigation menu:

1. **Home / Landing Page** (`landing-view`):
   - Hero header focusing on road safety statistics in India.
   - Core metrics based on Ministry of Road Transport and Highways (MoRTH) reports: **480,652 accidents**, **150,785 deaths**, **31.37% death ratio**, aiming to reduce to **0%**.
   - Interactive SVG/HTML emergency timeline demonstrating the golden-hour response mechanism.
2. **Project Overview** (`overview-view`):
   - Detailed review of the academic motivation, why this system is optimized for Indian roads (high vehicle density, chaotic driving, mixed vehicle classes), and the municipal CCTV integration workflow.
3. **Dataset Section** (`dataset-view`):
   - Details of the training dataset.
   - Pipeline records: `train.record` and `test.record`.
   - Annotation structure: Pascal VOC XML labels mapping to the `car accident` class defined in `accidents.pbtxt`.
4. **Model Architecture Section** (`architecture-view`):
   - Technical specifications of the SSD MobileNet V1 model.
   - Hyperparameter metrics table (RMSProp optimizer, initial learning rate of `0.004`, batch size `16`, decay rate `0.95`).
   - Interactive Mermaid architecture flowchart.
   - Mathematical model formulas (Multi-task Loss Combining localization L1 loss and classification confidence Sigmoid loss).
5. **Detection Console** (`dashboard-view`):
   - **CCTV Feed Tab**: Drag & drop traffic video/images, load mock Chennai road CCTV streams, run bounding box canvas overlays.
   - **Android App Emulator Tab**: A visual mobile smartphone shell. Features a 300x300 viewfinder, a 75x75 scaled thumbnail, text status log arrays (`[1] car accident (74%)`), custom threshold slider (default 60%), and a manual "Detect Object" button.
   - **Python CLI Emulator Tab**: An interactive terminal command simulator. Users type `python classifier.py input.jpg output.jpg` and see real TensorFlow init warning outputs, file logs, and output file directories.
   - **Results Dashboard**: Real-time evaluation of the processed feed (confidence score, severity, location coordinates, evaluation times).
   - **Alert Generation Module**: Console with mobilizers for 108 Ambulances, Traffic Police dispatch, and Trauma Unit Pre-Alerts.
6. **Analytics Hub** (`analytics-view`):
   - Interactive Leaflet.js GIS Map centered on high-density accident intersections in Chennai (Guindy, Koyambedu, Kathipara, Tambaram GST Road, OMR Sholinganallur).
   - Multi-axis monthly trend charts (Bar Chart) and incident severity ratios (Doughnut Chart) powered by Chart.js.
7. **Reports Center** (`reports-view`):
   - Dynamic report constructor allowing users to compile official incident logs, enter traffic notes, verify agency dispatches, and print/download formatted accident sheets.
8. **History Logs** (`history-view`):
   - Database of all system audits reading and writing from local browser storage, allowing search query lookups, severity filters, individual log deletion, and detailed print layouts.

